T*
(- System Model: What Atho Is Actually Enforcing) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Atho is a layered system where each stage has a narrow responsibility. That separation is) Tj
T*
(important because it prevents one component from becoming a hidden consensus authority.) Tj
T*
(- Interface layer \(GUI/API\): gathers inputs, normalizes payloads, and applies UX safeguards.) Tj
T*
(- Build layer: creates canonical transaction structures and fills witness/private vectors.) Tj
T*
(- Admission layer: mempool entry checks tx policy and basic validity.) Tj
T*
(- Verification layer: enforces ownership, signature validity, UTXO spend rules, and private note) Tj
T*
(semantics.) Tj
T*
(- Mining layer: selects mempool txs, applies block-mode transforms, builds coinbase, and mines.) Tj
T*
(- Block verification layer: recomputes commitments and checks accounting and structural) Tj
T*
(invariants.) Tj
T*
(- Commit layer: atomically updates state stores and journals.) Tj
T*
(- Wallet recovery layer: scans chain and decodes private receives for local ownership.) Tj
T*
ET
endstream
