(One bundle can receive unlimited private notes because each send includes fresh randomness and) Tj
T*
(context:) Tj
T*
(- sender performs Kyber encapsulation to receiver Kyber public key,) Tj
T*
(- this generates a per-output shared secret,) Tj
T*
(- recipient id and encrypted payload are derived from that shared secret,) Tj
T*
(- per-note Falcon child key in output is tied to encrypted note seed, not to a static) Tj
T*
(receiver-side counter.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(This means:) Tj
T*
(- receiver does not pre-generate all possible note keys,) Tj
T*
(- receiver scans outputs and attempts decapsulation/decryption,) Tj
T*
(- only outputs targeted to receiver bundle decode successfully.) Tj
