(Q2\) How does wallet know which child Falcon note keys to generate?) Tj
T*
(It does not pre-generate an infinite tree blindly. It scans chain outputs, decapsulates/decrypts) Tj
T*
(outputs addressed to its bundle, gets note seed from payload, then deterministically regenerates) Tj
T*
(that note Falcon keypair.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Q3\) If receiver reuses same bundle forever, how can notes stay unique?) Tj
T*
(Each sender encapsulation produces fresh shared secret and encrypted payload. Each note payload) Tj
T*
(carries note seed, producing per-note Falcon key uniqueness even under same receiver bundle.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Q4\) What is the role of account/counter in private note derivation?) Tj
T*
(On sender side, they define deterministic sequence for note seed reservation from sender master) Tj
T*
(seed. This ensures deterministic, non-colliding note generation across sends.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Q5\) Why enforce x-address and bundle-hash binding?) Tj
T*
(To prevent malformed or substituted recipient bundle data. X-address is deterministic encoding) Tj
T*
(of bundle hash; mismatch means reject.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Q6\) Where is replay prevention for private spends?) Tj
T*
(Nullifier uniqueness at verifier and state-store layers; consumed nullifier cannot be spent) Tj
T*
(again.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Q7\) Why include view tags if we already have recipient id checks?) Tj
T*
(Performance. View tags are fast reject filters before expensive decapsulation/decryption and) Tj
T*
(full validation.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Q8\) Why are private tx larger than public tx?) Tj
T*
(They carry encrypted payload and private vectors with additional cryptographic context. This is) Tj
T*
(expected tradeoff for privacy.) Tj
T*
() Tj
